":"Newtown (Cambridge), Massachusetts","dates":"1634","notes":"Chosen at general town meeting Feb 4, 1634 along with Haynes, Bradstreet, and four others"},{"title":"Representative","jurisdiction":"Massachusetts Bay General Court","dates":"1634-1636","notes":"One of Representatives for Newtown (Cambridge), May 14, 1634"},{"title":"Deputy","jurisdiction":"Connecticut General Court, Hartford","dates":"1637-1653"},{"title":"Treasurer","jurisdiction":"Colony of Connecticut","dates":"1652, 1654-1656, 1659"},{"title":"Assistant","jurisdiction":"Colony of Connecticut","dates":"1654-1659"},{"title":"Commissioner","jurisdiction":"United Colonies","dates":"1656-1658"}],"emigration":{"ship":"Lyon","departure":"England, June 22, 1632","arrival":"Boston, September 16, 1632","commander":"Captain Mason","passengers":123,"notes":"123 passengers including 50 children; all arrived in good health after 12-week passage. Fellow passengers included William Wadsworth, Tobie Willet (possible relation to Mary Willet who married Rev. Samuel Hooker), James Olmstedd, and others of Hooker's Company."},"hartford_land":{"inventory_date":"February 1639/40","parcels":9,"notes":"Nine parcels originally granted: dwelling house on east side of Main Street abutting Centinel Hill; seven acres east of Great River; five acres in North Meadow; forty-seven acres meadow/swamp in North Meadow; one acre in Little Meadow; thirty acres in Old Oxpasture; seventeen acres in Cow Pasture; eleven acres in Venturers Field; sixteen acres in Neck of Land. Also gained 25 additional parcels by acquisition."},"will":{"date":{"year":1659,"month":8,"day":12},"codicil_date":{"year":1660,"month":1,"day":17},"bequests_summary":"Dwelling house and lands to wife Dorothy for her natural life; then to son John. Wethersfield property to son Samuel. Grandchildren John Russell (£20), John Talcott, Samuel Talcott, Elizabeth Talcott (£5 each). £5 to Rev. Samuel Stone; £5 toward a Latin school at Hartford. Overseers: Richard Lord Sr. and 